```
You are an expert in React, TypeScript, Supabase, Tailwind CSS, and Lucide React for a Lost & Found Management System.

Code Style and Structure
- Write clean, maintainable React TypeScript code with practical examples.
- Use functional components with hooks; avoid class components.
- Implement proper error handling with descriptive messages for user feedback.
- Use descriptive, semantic variable names (e.g., isLoading, hasError, isClaimed).
- Structure components logically: main component, sub-components, utility functions, types.

Naming Conventions
- Use PascalCase for component files (e.g., ItemCard.tsx, ClaimForm.tsx).
- Use camelCase for utility functions and variables.
- Export components as named exports for better imports.

TypeScript Usage
- Use TypeScript interfaces for component props and database models.
- Define clear interfaces for Supabase database tables.
- Use proper type annotations for all functions and variables.
- Implement type safety for API responses and form submissions.

Supabase Integration
- Use typed queries with proper error handling for all database operations.
- Implement storage bucket operations with progress indicators.
- Handle authentication with proper session management.
- Follow RLS (Row Level Security) patterns for data access control.

UI and Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS for responsive styling with mobile-first approach.
- Implement Lucide React icons consistently across the application.
- Create reusable UI components for common patterns.
- Maintain consistent color schemes using Tailwind's yellow-500 as primary color.

Image Processing
- Resize all uploaded images to 512x512px max dimensions.
- Maintain aspect ratio during image resizing.
- Use 90% quality for compressed images.
- Implement progress indicators for uploads.
- Clean up orphaned images when operations fail.

Performance Optimization
- Implement proper loading states with visual indicators.
- Use proper React state management to avoid unnecessary rerenders.
- Optimize image loading with appropriate sizing and formats.
- Implement pagination or infinite scrolling for large item collections.

Form Handling
- Implement proper form validation for all user inputs.
- Provide clear feedback for form submission states.
- Use controlled components for form inputs.
- Implement proper error handling for API requests.

Navigation and Routing
- Use React Router with proper route protection.
- Implement clean navigation patterns with history management.
- Provide breadcrumbs or back buttons for improved user experience.

Follow modern React patterns and Supabase documentation for authentication, storage, and database operations.
